    "title": {
      "rendered": "How to Create a Custom Snapcode for Your Nonprofit"
    },
    "content": {
      "rendered": "<p><strong><a href=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/11/How-to-Create-a-Custom-Snapcode-for-Your-Nonprofit.jpg\"><img data-recalc-dims=\"1\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"alignright size-medium wp-image-18704\" src=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/11/How-to-Create-a-Custom-Snapcode-for-Your-Nonprofit-300x300.jpg?resize=300%2C300\" alt=\"How to Create a Custom Snapcode for Your Nonprofit\" width=\"300\" height=\"300\" srcset=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/11/How-to-Create-a-Custom-Snapcode-for-Your-Nonprofit.jpg?resize=300%2C300&amp;ssl=1 300w, https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/11/How-to-Create-a-Custom-Snapcode-for-Your-Nonprofit.jpg?resize=150%2C150&amp;ssl=1 150w, https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/11/How-to-Create-a-Custom-Snapcode-for-Your-Nonprofit.jpg?resize=200%2C200&amp;ssl=1 200w, https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/11/How-to-Create-a-Custom-Snapcode-for-Your-Nonprofit.jpg?resize=75%2C75&amp;ssl=1 75w, https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/11/How-to-Create-a-Custom-Snapcode-for-Your-Nonprofit.jpg?w=1024&amp;ssl=1 1024w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 300px) 100vw, 300px\" /></a><a href=\"http://snapchat.com\" target=\"_blank\">Snapchat</a></strong> is a mobile\u00a0app where users share snaps with one another, but unlike other visual social networks, the snaps\u00a0<em>disappear</em>\u00a0once they are viewed. Launched in 2011, many nonprofits have been hesitant to experiment with a mobile social network where content disappears and where no traditional &#8220;Follow&#8221; functionality exists. But with <strong><a href=\"http://expandedramblings.com/index.php/snapchat-statistics/\" target=\"_blank\">100 million daily active users</a>\u00a0</strong>and the launch of\u00a0<strong><a href=\"https://support.snapchat.com/ca/stories\" target=\"_blank\">Stories</a></strong> (a collection of snaps that can be viewed for 24 hours), a few early adopter nonprofits are experimenting\u00a0with Snapchat and their efforts are worth watching.</p>\n<p>The vast majority of nonprofits will find Snapchat\u00a0challenging. You need unique, real-time content that appeals to Snapchat&#8217;s<strong> <a href=\"http://www.businessinsider.com/a-15-year-old-explains-why-teens-are-obsessed-with-snapchat-and-instagram-is-over-2015-5\" target=\"_blank\">teen and millennial user base</a> </strong>and that requires time and resources that many nonprofits simply do not have. At\u00a0the very least nonprofit social media managers should set up an account, reserve their username, and &#8220;Add&#8221; early adopter nonprofits in order to study how the app works and observe what the early adopters\u00a0are doing on Snapchat. It will be interesting to see if in time <a href=\"https://support.snapchat.com/ca/snapcash\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>Snapcash</strong></a>\u00a0becomes useful for fundraising or if text or web-based content becomes more integrated into the Snapchat tool set.</p>\n<h2><strong>How to Add Friends on Snapchat Using Snapcodes</strong></h2>\n<p>If your nonprofit decides to become active on Snapchat, you can build a following by either promoting your <strong>username\u00a0(dosomething, onecampaign, savethechildren, unicef, WWF_DK)\u00a0or your Snapcode (see examples below)</strong> which functions as QR code within the Snapchat app. Snapchat users can then add your nonprofit as a friend by searching for your username or by tapping\u00a0a screenshot of your nonprofit&#8217;s Snapcode in their Camera Roll:</p>\n<table>\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<th><a href=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/11/Add-Friends-Snapchat.jpg\"><img data-recalc-dims=\"1\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"size-full wp-image-18700 aligncenter\" style=\"border: 1px solid black;\" src=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/11/Add-Friends-Snapchat.jpg?resize=292%2C519\" alt=\"Add Friends Snapchat\" width=\"292\" height=\"519\" srcset=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/11/Add-Friends-Snapchat.jpg?w=292&amp;ssl=1 292w, https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/11/Add-Friends-Snapchat.jpg?resize=169%2C300&amp;ssl=1 169w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 292px) 100vw, 292px\" /></a></th>\n<th colspan=\"2\"><a href=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/11/camera-roll-1.png\"><img data-recalc-dims=\"1\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-18710\" style=\"border: 1px solid black;\" src=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/11/camera-roll-1.png?resize=292%2C521\" alt=\"camera roll 1\" width=\"292\" height=\"521\" srcset=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/11/camera-roll-1.png?w=292&amp;ssl=1 292w, https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/11/camera-roll-1.png?resize=168%2C300&amp;ssl=1 168w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 292px) 100vw, 292px\" /></a></th>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n<h2><strong>How to Create a Custom Snapcode for Your Nonprofit</strong></h2>\n<p>To avoid looking like exactly like millions of other Snapcodes (yellow background, black dots, white ghost), it&#8217;s highly recommended that you customize your nonprofit&#8217;s Snapcode:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Using your Snapchat login,\u00a0<strong><a href=\"http://accounts.snapchat.com/accounts/snapcodes\" target=\"_blank\">download a .PNG file of your Snapcode</a></strong>.</li>\n<li>Use a photo editing such as <strong><a href=\"https://www.canva.com/\" target=\"_blank\">Canva</a></strong> or <strong><a href=\"http://www.photoshop.com/\" target=\"_blank\">Photoshop</a>\u00a0</strong>(to change the background color of your Snapcode) to drag and drop your nonprofit&#8217;s logo or avatar inside of the Snapchat ghost. You must\u00a0stay within the black lines of the white ghost for your Snapcode will work.</li>\n<li>Save your new Snapcode as a .JPEG, .GIF, and/or .PNG and then promote it online and in email.</li>\n<li>You can also use\u00a0<strong><a href=\"http://snaptageditor.com/\" target=\"_blank\">snaptageditor.com</a></strong> to easily create a custom Snapcode.</li>\n</ul>\n<h2>Five Examples of Custom Snapcodes</h2>\n<p>To add these nonprofits and Nonprofit Tech for Good on Snapchat, simply screenshot the Snapcodes and then add them in the Snapchat app.</p>\n<h2 style=\"text-align: center;\">1. CARE</h2>\n<p><a href=\"https://twitter.com/care\" target=\"_blank\"><img data-recalc-dims=\"1\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-18712\" src=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/11/CARE.jpg?resize=512%2C512\" alt=\"CARE\" width=\"512\" height=\"512\" srcset=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/11/CARE.jpg?w=512&amp;ssl=1 512w, https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/11/CARE.jpg?resize=150%2C150&amp;ssl=1 150w, https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/11/CARE.jpg?resize=300%2C300&amp;ssl=1 300w, https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/11/CARE.jpg?resize=200%2C200&amp;ssl=1 200w, https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/11/CARE.jpg?resize=75%2C75&amp;ssl=1 75w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 512px) 100vw, 512px\" /></a></p>\n<h2 style=\"text-align: center;\">2. Get Schooled</h2>\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><a href=\"https://twitter.com/getschooled\" target=\"_blank\"><img data-recalc-dims=\"1\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-18713\" src=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/11/Get-Schooled.jpg?resize=512%2C512\" alt=\"Get Schooled\" width=\"512\" height=\"512\" srcset=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/11/Get-Schooled.jpg?w=512&amp;ssl=1 512w, https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/11/Get-Schooled.jpg?resize=150%2C150&amp;ssl=1 150w, https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/11/Get-Schooled.jpg?resize=300%2C300&amp;ssl=1 300w, https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/11/Get-Schooled.jpg?resize=200%2C200&amp;ssl=1 200w, https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/11/Get-Schooled.jpg?resize=75%2C75&amp;ssl=1 75w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 512px) 100vw, 512px\" /></a></p>\n<h2 style=\"text-align: center;\">3. NPR</h2>\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><a href=\"https://twitter.com/NPR\" target=\"_blank\"><img data-recalc-dims=\"1\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-18714\" src=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/11/nprnews.png?resize=512%2C512\" alt=\"nprnews\" width=\"512\" height=\"512\" srcset=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/11/nprnews.png?w=512&amp;ssl=1 512w, https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/11/nprnews.png?resize=150%2C150&amp;ssl=1 150w, https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/11/nprnews.png?resize=300%2C300&amp;ssl=1 300w, https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/11/nprnews.png?resize=200%2C200&amp;ssl=1 200w, https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/11/nprnews.png?resize=75%2C75&amp;ssl=1 75w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 512px) 100vw, 512px\" /></a></p>\n<h2 style=\"text-align: center;\">4. Nonprofit Tech for Good</h2>\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><a href=\"https://twitter.com/nonprofitorgs\" target=\"_blank\"><img data-recalc-dims=\"1\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-18715\" src=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/11/nonprofitorgs-snapcode-jpg.jpg?resize=512%2C512\" alt=\"nonprofitorgs snapcode jpg\" width=\"512\" height=\"512\" srcset=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/11/nonprofitorgs-snapcode-jpg.jpg?w=512&amp;ssl=1 512w, https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/11/nonprofitorgs-snapcode-jpg.jpg?resize=150%2C150&amp;ssl=1 150w, https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/11/nonprofitorgs-snapcode-jpg.jpg?resize=300%2C300&amp;ssl=1 300w, https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/11/nonprofitorgs-snapcode-jpg.jpg?resize=200%2C200&amp;ssl=1 200w, https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/11/nonprofitorgs-snapcode-jpg.jpg?resize=75%2C75&amp;ssl=1 75w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 512px) 100vw, 512px\" /></a></p>\n<h2 style=\"text-align: center;\">5. Society for Science</h2>\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><a href=\"https://twitter.com/Society4Science\" target=\"_blank\"><img data-recalc-dims=\"1\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-18716\" src=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/11/Scoiety-for-Science.png?resize=512%2C512\" alt=\"Scoiety for Science\" width=\"512\" height=\"512\" srcset=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/11/Scoiety-for-Science.png?w=512&amp;ssl=1 512w, https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/11/Scoiety-for-Science.png?resize=150%2C150&amp;ssl=1 150w, https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/11/Scoiety-for-Science.png?resize=300%2C300&amp;ssl=1 300w, https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/11/Scoiety-for-Science.png?resize=200%2C200&amp;ssl=1 200w, https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/11/Scoiety-for-Science.png?resize=75%2C75&amp;ssl=1 75w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 512px) 100vw, 512px\" /></a></p>\n<hr />\n<h2 style=\"text-align: center;\"><strong style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 17px;\"><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><span style=\"font-family: Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 18px; font-weight: bold;\"><em>Mobile for Good: A How-To Fundraising Guide for Nonprofits</em></span></span></strong></h2>\n<p><a href=\"http://www.amazon.com/Mobile-Good-How--Fundraising-Nonprofits/dp/0071825460\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"alignleft wp-image-16024\" style=\"margin: 10px; border: 1px solid black;\" src=\" http://www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/10/mobile-for-good-with-ribbon.jpg\" alt=\"mobile for good look inside\" width=\"99\" height=\"150\" /></a>Based on more than 20 years of experience and 25,000+ hours spent utilizing mobile and social media, <a href=\"http://www.amazon.com/Mobile-Good-How--Fundraising-Nonprofits/dp/0071825460\"><em><strong>Mobile for Good: A How-To Fundraising Guide for Nonprofits</strong></em></a> is a comprehensive 256-page book packed with more than 500 best practices. Written on the premise that all communications and fundraising are now mobile and social, Mobile for Good is a step-by-step how-to guide for writing, implementing, and maintaining a mobile and social fundraising strategy for your nonprofit.</p>\n",
